
This directory is intended for PlatformIO Test Runner and project tests.

Unit Testing is a software testing method by which individual units of
source code, sets of one or more MCU program modules together with associated
control data, usage procedures, and operating procedures, are tested to
determine whether they are fit for use. Unit testing finds problems early
in the development cycle.

More information about PlatformIO Unit Testing:
- https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/advanced/unit-testing/index.html

This is a simple project that uses the ESP32-WROOM-32E board with I2C LCD 1602 
and DHT11 to create a simple monitor that display live data of the temperature 
and humidity of the environment on the LCD through the data received by the 
DHT11.

The circuit is built by attaching the 3.3V of ESP32 board to the Vcc of the DHT11,
GPIO4 to Data pin. 5.0V is attached to the Vcc of the LCD, the SCL and SDA are attached
as well to the corresponding pinout of the ESP32 board. GND of both the DHT11 and LCD 
should be attached to the same GND node on the ESP32. 

Necessary Libraries:
  DHT sensor library
  Adafruit Unified Sensor
  LiquidCrystal_I2C